rest_of_day_open: I see it going decently well, where I will get some much needed chores done and hopefully not too many obstacles from the recent lockdowns that are reoccurring. As long as I stay safe, I think my week will be a very accomplished one, and I'll hopefully get things done that I've been needing to finish for months now!
critical_positive: We were both very friendly and bubbly with each other, and both of us had an idea on what to talk about and how to go about certain topics. It helped that we are in the same state and so found lots of commonalities. The conversation was really giving and we both contributed heavily together.
critical_negative: I sometimes interrupted the conversation to give a compliment or praise as she was talking. Sometimes it was hard to see her webcam and so I couldn't tell if she started speaking yet, and so I would go in and talk and realize she was about to. It got bad at some points because we would hiccup with each others sentences and figuring out who should speak first.

rest_of_day_open: About the same as the past few weeks. Nothing awful, a few cases of things going extremely well, and lots of just keeping on keeping on. I’m in one of the states with the highest number of coronavirus cases, so I’m not going to be getting out or doing anything out of the ordinary any time soon, but I have settled into a COVID routine.
critical_positive: We were both friendly and warm to each other from the start. We had a lot in common, not only being involved in UserTesting, but also living in Arizona and liking similar sorts of books. Surprisingly, there really were no down moments in our conversation—we hit it off from the start,
critical_negative: Unlike the last time I did this, there really weren’t any conversational lags or awkward moments. I know that sounds really unlikely, but we really did have a good, successful conversation for the entire 25 minutes this time. We weren’t uncomfortable with each other, as I usually am at first when connecting with a complete stranger.
